;
;I# 1578 : map
INUMBER 1578
NAME 1060
WEIGHT 1
VOLUME 1
SUBSTANCE PAPER
*DESCRIPTION_START READ
You carefully examine the map...
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVERB GAZE -1
	IFVAR INTNUM3 = 1
		ECHO PLAYER This is a multimap item. Set ITEMBIT0 to 1 if you want it to be anything other than the Deep Realms Map
		ECHO PLAYER Then add the map you want to the end of the item and set an itembit to check
	ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVAR ITEMBIT0 ! 1
  IFVERB READ -1
     CLEARVERB
     ECHO PLAYER    Deep Realms -- Surface Entrance. As Recorded by Menelian the Sage.
     ECHO PLAYER                                 X..# <-ladder
     ECHO PLAYER                                    .
     ECHO PLAYER                                     .
     ECHO PLAYER                                      . ...
     ECHO PLAYER                                       .. .
     ECHO PLAYER                                               .
     ECHO PLAYER                                                 .
     ECHO PLAYER                                                 --
     ECHO PLAYER                              ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~||~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
     ECHO PLAYER                          ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~||~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
     ECHO PLAYER                       ~~~~~~                    --
     ECHO PLAYER                    ~~~~r
     ECHO PLAYER                 ~~~~a
     ECHO PLAYER             ~~~~m
     ECHO PLAYER          ~~~~n
     ECHO PLAYER        ~~~i
     ECHO PLAYER      ~~~t                                      Fayd
     ECHO PLAYER    ~~~l                                         |
     ECHO PLAYER ~~~ E                                          \|/
     ECHO PLAYER ~~                                              S%c
     ECHO PLAYER The map describes a precise crevice to enter through to reach a cave.
     EQUAL INTNUM25 1
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVAR ITEMBIT0 = 1
 IFVAR ITEMBIT1 = 1
  IFVERB READ -1
     CLEARVERB
     ECHO PLAYER    Technomancer's Base as recorded by Katherine Wahl from Hero's Hill
     ECHO PLAYER    in the month of Banamea of 1039                             
     ECHO PLAYER                                    
     ECHO PLAYER                            .........  
     ECHO PLAYER                          .  O Sphere 1
     ECHO PLAYER                         .     ...   O .    
     ECHO PLAYER                        . O   .   .     .   
     ECHO PLAYER               Wall => .       ...     O .                                  
     ECHO PLAYER                      . O                 . 
     ECHO PLAYER                      .      ---------  O .
     ECHO PLAYER                      . O    |       |    .     
     ECHO PLAYER                      .      | Gate  |  O .
     ECHO PLAYER                      . O    |       |    .                
     ECHO PLAYER      O = Towers      .      ---------  O .
     ECHO PLAYER                      . O     Sphere 2    .
     ECHO PLAYER                       .        ...      .
     ECHO PLAYER                        . O    .   .  O .      
     ECHO PLAYER                         .      ...    .
     ECHO PLAYER                           .  O  O  O .
     ECHO PLAYER                              .......
     ECHO PLAYER The map describes the locations of the structures inside the base.
  ENDIF
ENDIF 
;
;I# 1579 : cottage
INUMBER 1579
NAME 1059
WEIGHT 1000
VOLUME 1000
*DESCRIPTION_START
The cottage is constructed of mirmach logs and has a thatched roof. Some smoke rises from its chimney. Gazing through the window, you see that it is pretty messy inside. An oak door allows entrance.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
;I# 1369 : general ore
INUMBER 1369
NAME 1064
ORE
PARAMETER1 0
PARAMETER2 1370
WEIGHT 40
VOLUME 8
ARTICLE SOME
IFPREVERB ANALYZE -1
        CLEARVERB
        IFVAR ROUNDTIME ! 0
                STRCVT 0 ROUNDTIME
                ECHO PLAYER [Wait %0 seconds...]
        ENDIF
        IFVAR ROUNDTIME = 0
                IFVAR SKILL35 = 0
                        ECHO PLAYER You wouldn't know where to begin.
                ENDIF
                IFVAR SKILL35 > 0
                        IFVAR SKILL35 < 3
                                ECHO PLAYER You don't have enough experience as a miner yet to analyze ore.
                        ENDIF
                        IFVAR SKILL35 > 2
                                IFVAR WIELDED ! 766
                                        ECHO PLAYER You gaze at the ore, trying to assess its purity based on what you can see on its surface.%c[Round: 5 sec]
                                        ECHO OTHERS %N gazes at %a.
                                        EQUAL ROUNDTIME 5
                                        ECHO PLAYER You can't tell anything about this ore from looking at the surface.
                                ENDIF
                                IFVAR WIELDED = 766
                                        ECHO PLAYER You tap a small chip off the ore and examine its cross section.%c[Round: 5 sec]
                                        ECHO OTHERS %N users a miner's hammer to chip off a tiny sample of %a and examines the little piece.
                                        EQUAL ROUNDTIME 5
                                        RANDOM DUMMY1 1 30 0
                                        IFVAR DUMMY1 > 28
                                                RANDOM DUMMY1 1 100 0
                                        ENDIF
                                        EQUAL DUMMY2 ITEMVAL3
                                        DIV DUMMY2 10
                                        SUB DUMMY1 DUMMY2
                                        IFVAR DUMMY1 > SKILL35
                                                RANDOM DUMMY2 1 5 3
                                        ENDIF
                                        IFVAR DUMMY2 < 1
                                                ECHO PLAYER You wouldn't even use this ore as a doorstop.
                                        ENDIF
                                        IFVAR DUMMY2 = 1
                                                ECHO PLAYER This ore is of the poorest possible quality, hardly worth the name.
                                        ENDIF
                                        IFVAR DUMMY2 = 2
                                                ECHO PLAYER This ore is of very poor quality, under thirty percent pure.
                                        ENDIF
                                        IFVAR DUMMY2 = 3
                                                ECHO PLAYER This ore is of very poor quality, well under fifty percent pure.
                                        ENDIF
                                        IFVAR DUMMY2 = 4
                                                ECHO PLAYER This ore is of poor quality, just under fifty percent pure.
                                        ENDIF
                                        IFVAR DUMMY2 = 5
                                                ECHO PLAYER This ore is barely passable, just over fifty percent pure.
                                        ENDIF
                                        IFVAR DUMMY2 = 6
                                                ECHO PLAYER This ore is passable, over fifty percent pure.
                                        ENDIF
                                        IFVAR DUMMY2 = 7
                                                ECHO PLAYER This ore is all right, over seventy percent pure.
                                        ENDIF
                                        IFVAR DUMMY2 = 8
                                                ECHO PLAYER This ore is quite good, over eighty percent pure.
                                        ENDIF
                                        IFVAR DUMMY2 = 9
                                                ECHO PLAYER This ore is of excellent quality, nearly one hundred percent pure.
                                        ENDIF
                                        IFVAR DUMMY2 > 9
                                                ECHO PLAYER This ore is among the most beautiful you've seen in your life... it is nearly solid metal.
                                        ENDIF
                                ENDIF
                        ENDIF
                ENDIF
        ENDIF
ENDIF
