;
;
; Lyre (New and improved)
INUMBER 299
NAME 654
MISC
WORN_DON
WEIGHT 1
VOLUME 1
TURNABLE
SUBSTANCE SOFTMETAL
IFVERB PLAY -1
        IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 0
        EQUAL ITEMVAL1 1
        ENDIF
        IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 1
        ECHO PLAYER You begin to play a mournful melody. The notes swell and drop as you weave the dirge. Sadness seems to ooze right out of your fingers.
        ECHO OTHERS %N beings to play %h lyre. The somber notes of a beautifully played dirge reach your ears. The air fills with sadness.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 2
        ECHO PLAYER You pluck out a fast-paced jig on your lyre. Your fingers blur and your feet begin to tap. This music is perfect for dancing.
        ECHO OTHERS Fast paced dancing music erupts from %N. %s is playing a jig on %h lyre. Unconciously, your feet begin to tap.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 3
        ECHO PLAYER You play a long and storied ballad on your lyre. You sing to it as well, telling a story of a time long gone by.
        ECHO OTHERS %N sings and old ballad and plays accompaniment on %h lyre. It is a story of history and heroism from times long since past.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 4
        ECHO PLAYER You strum your lyre, playing mostly chords and not much melody. The affect creates calming background music for you and those around you.
        ECHO OTHERS %N strums %h lyre. Playing calming background music. It is very relaxing.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 5
        ECHO PLAYER You play a grand tune on your lyre. Focusing heavily on the downbeats and playing long notes, you weave a rousing tune worthy of royalty.
        ECHO OTHERS %N plays a grand and rousing tune on %h lyre. It reminds you of procession music and you instinctively look around for someone with a title.
        ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB CONCENTRATE -1
        CLEARVERB
        ADD ITEMVAL1 1
        IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 6
        EQUAL ITEMVAL1 1
        ENDIF
        IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 1
        ECHO PLAYER You prepare to play a somber dirge.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 2
        ECHO PLAYER You prepare to play an upbeat jig.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 3
        ECHO PLAYER You prepare to play a long ballad of olde.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 4
        ECHO PLAYER You prepare to play some relaxing background music.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 5
        ECHO PLAYER You prepare to play a grand melody.
        ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB TURN -1
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER You take great care to tune your lyre.
        ECHO OTHERS %N turns some knobs, attempting to capture perfect pitch.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB RUB -1
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER You polish the wood part of your lyre.
        ECHO OTHERS %N polishes %h lyre.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PULL -1
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER You pluck out one single note on the lyre.
        ECHO OTHERS Twang! %N plucks a lyre string.
ENDIF
;

