INUMBER 1007
NAME 1401
MISC
WEIGHT 1
VOLUME 1
SUBSTANCE PAPER
*DESCRIPTION_START EXAMINE
The faded parchment crinkles in your hands.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFPREVERB READ -1
  IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 0
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER      My end is near, the wasting disease which is my reward for defeating
  ECHO PLAYER the Vampire Lords destroying my body and will to live. I have one chance,
  ECHO PLAYER the pool which Tilvaen Treegrower discovered. My research has unearthed what
  ECHO PLAYER I believe to be its location. I set out tomorrow with my four companions.
  ECHO PLAYER ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ECHO PLAYER      The misery of the Wastelands offer no refuge to us. I fear that we are
  ECHO PLAYER all at the end of our ropes. I have begun to wonder if my disease is
  ECHO PLAYER affecting my mental faculties. I have been experiencing strange visions and
  ECHO PLAYER even stranger dreams. Our water is nearly at an end, and hope dies slowly.
  ECHO PLAYER ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ECHO PLAYER      Loril died today. Buying time for us to escape from the Sandgorgon with
  ECHO PLAYER his life. Oh brave Loril! My vaunted power as the Arcana Guildmaster brought
  ECHO PLAYER down by the disease which is taking my life. I wonder if I should lay down
  ECHO PLAYER to die and order the rest of my companions back to Fayd. Shemri bless you
  ECHO PLAYER Loril, may you find the peace you always searched for.
  ECHO PLAYER ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ECHO PLAYER      Saved! Hope has sprung anew at this blessed place that we discovered in
  ECHO PLAYER the depths of the Wastelands. The Sister's of the Earthmother have taken us
  ECHO PLAYER into their bosom, and even as I write our wounds heal and our energy grows.
  ECHO PLAYER My disease still progresses, unabated, but I now feel that there is real
  ECHO PLAYER hope. We continue our journey tomorrow, heading....
  ENDIF
ENDIF
