INUMBER 1539
NAME 1401
MISC
WEIGHT 1
VOLUME 1
SUBSTANCE PAPER
*DESCRIPTION_START READ
     These will be my final words, as I now know that I will only live a
few hours more. I have sent Elvinar, Pietro, and Ferovian away with the
three items I used to defeat the Triad the last time. It is my hope that
they will hide the items, The Cross of Shemri, the Amulet of Damalar, and
the Ring of Nirvok, in safe places so that they can be found if the need
for them arises again.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
     Of the Triad I will say this, their final defeat can only be
accomplished through the death of the dread Vampire Overlord, Krangvak.
My research into Krangvak and his origin hint of an alien being from another
dimension. This dimension is filled with Vampiric beings akin to Krangvak,
but Krangvak is the worst of his kind.
     To fully defeat this abomination requires fighting and destroying it
in its own dimension. Only then can the horrible curse of the Triad be
lifted from this beautiful world.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
     I go now to my final reward, a place in blessed Shemri's realm. To
those who come after me, I leave you with this, "Use not the Power for
Power's sake, instead strive to ever use it for the benefit of our world."
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
INUMBER 1540
NAME 1401
MISC
WEIGHT 1
VOLUME 1
SUBSTANCE PAPER
*DESCRIPTION_START READ
    Excerpt from Beasts of Andor
    ----------------------------

SANDGORGON:
----------
      The Sandgorgon of the Wastelands is an almost mythical beast.
Some think it to be a creature conjured by mother's to keep their children
from wandering into the Wastelands. What we know is that it is a beast of
horrendous power. Perhaps created during the period of the Cataclysm it
roams the Wastelands single-mindedly searching for food. Rumors have it
absorbing the souls of those it slays, thus continually increasing its
horrible power. Descriptions of the Sandgorgon vary from an immense Dragon
to a horrible sandcloud. None know for sure as no one has ever seen it and
survived.
*DESCRIPTION_END
